job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, weâ€™re committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. ðŸ“ˆ Start-up equity ðŸ¦· Full health, vision & dental coverage ðŸ½ï¸ Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees ðŸš Commuter benefit ðŸš  Team building events & happy hours ðŸŒ´ Flexible PTO ðŸ’» Apple equipment plus home office budget ðŸ’¸ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We encourage all candidates to apply even if your experience doesn't exactly match up to our job description. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. We look forward to hearing from you!

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. job.job_description: Company Description: McDonaldâ€™s growth strategy, Accelerating the Arches, encompasses all aspects of our business as the leading global omni-channel restaurant brand. As the consumer landscape shifts we are using our competitive advantages to further strengthen our brand. One of our core growth strategies is to Double Down on the 3Ds (Delivery, Digital and Drive Thru). McDonaldâ€™s will accelerate technology innovation so 65M+ customers a day will experience a fast, easy experience, whether at one of our 25,000 and growing Drive thrus, through McDelivery, dine-in or takeaway. McDonaldâ€™s Global Technology is here to power tomorrowâ€™s feel-good moments. Thatâ€™s why youâ€™ll find us at the forefront of transformative technology, exploring new and innovative ways to serve our millions of customers and spread happiness one delicious Hot Fudge Sundae-dipped fry at a time. Using AI, robotics and emerging tech, weâ€™re digitizing the Golden Arches. Combine that with our unparalleled global scale, and weâ€™re reshaping all areas of the business, industry and every community that is home to a McDonaldâ€™s restaurant. We face complex tech challenges every day. But thatâ€™s where our diverse and talented teams come in. Theyâ€™re made up of the best and brightest from all over the globe, and they thrive in the space where feel-good meets fast-paced. Check out the McDonaldâ€™s Global Technology Technical Blog to learn how technology and our global team are directly enabling the Accelerating the Arches strategy. Department Overview McDonaldâ€™s, one of the most recognized brands in the world, is seeking a skilled Software Development Engineer to lead the development of our in-store technology as part of Commercial Product & Platform organization. The Commercial Product & Platform vision develops global technology products and platforms that delight our customers and enable our crews to operate our restaurants reliably and effectively. The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing and maintenance of the McDonaldâ€™s restaurant software. Restaurant Technology software includes application user interface, API layer software, data management, and data communication with external systems. The software needs to meet stringent reliability and performance requirements as well as the needs of our customers. The biggest area of increase in our spending has been in technology, which is helping to drive our growth. Weâ€™re looking at how to use technology to improve the customer experience and build new customer experiences. Weâ€™re also exploring technologies that can help us reduce or eliminate repetitive tasks and make employeesâ€™ jobs more exciting and rewarding. With all the new projects and initiatives, it is an exciting time to be on the team that is helping to make a Better McDonald's!Accountabilities & Responsibilities Develop marketing automation workflows focused on marketing communications & experience personalization such as push notifications, emails, and mobile app personalized experiences Conceptualize customer segmentation to support Marketing Automation based on knowledge of pre-existing data structures Translate business requests for marketing capabilities, into clear technical requirements that include data properties needed for implementing marketing automations Technical requirement solicitation and documentation skills to effectively capture and communicate marketing automation solutions/initiatives to key collaborators Ensure that all technical work aligns with the business objectives and marketing strategies Triage issues and defects - capturing, prioritizing and remediating for marketing automations Qualifications Basic Qualifications: Bachelorâ€™s Degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, or similar engineering field or equivalent years of experience. Minimum 1+ years of non-internship professional marketing automation experience with a marketing or advertising automation technology system Experience in implementing marketing automation elements such as segments, audiences, and decision-splits Basic understanding of marketing automation concepts and design principles â€“ proven track record to understand how structured data can be translated into marketing segments and other automations that provide personalized experiences/communications to customers Understanding of core technologies for web content development- HTML, CSS, and JavaScript Extensive experience in working with key data interchange formats including JSON and XML, demonstrating a strong ability to integrate, manipulate, and manage complex data structures across diverse systems and applications Ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams in sophisticated environments Excellent documentation and communication skills to bridge the gap between business strategy and technical teams. Hands on experience with JIRA/Confluence expected Preferred Skills:...

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, weâ€™re committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. ðŸ“ˆ Start-up equity ðŸ¦· Full health, vision & dental coverage ðŸ½ï¸ Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees ðŸš Commuter benefit ðŸš  Team building events & happy hours ðŸŒ´ Flexible PTO ðŸ’» Apple equipment plus home office budget ðŸ’¸ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We encourage all candidates to apply even if your experience doesn't exactly match up to our job description. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

job.job_description: Company Description: McDonaldâ€™s growth strategy, Accelerating the Arches, encompasses all aspects of our business as the leading global omni-channel restaurant brand. As the consumer landscape shifts we are using our competitive advantages to further strengthen our brand. One of our core growth strategies is to Double Down on the 3Ds (Delivery, Digital and Drive Thru). McDonaldâ€™s will accelerate technology innovation so 65M+ customers a day will experience a fast, easy experience, whether at one of our 25,000 and growing Drive thrus, through McDelivery, dine-in or takeaway. McDonaldâ€™s Global Technology is here to power tomorrowâ€™s feel-good moments. Thatâ€™s why youâ€™ll find us at the forefront of transformative technology, exploring new and innovative ways to serve our millions of customers and spread happiness one delicious Hot Fudge Sundae-dipped fry at a time. Using AI, robotics and emerging tech, weâ€™re digitizing the Golden Arches. Combine that with our unparalleled global scale, and weâ€™re reshaping all areas of the business, industry and every community that is home to a McDonaldâ€™s restaurant. We face complex tech challenges every day. But thatâ€™s where our diverse and talented teams come in. Theyâ€™re made up of the best and brightest from all over the globe, and they thrive in the space where feel-good meets fast-paced. Check out the McDonaldâ€™s Global Technology Technical Blog to learn how technology and our global team are directly enabling the Accelerating the Arches strategy. Department Overview McDonaldâ€™s, one of the most recognized brands in the world, is seeking a skilled Software Development Engineer to lead the development of our in-store technology as part of Commercial Product & Platform organization. The Commercial Product & Platform vision develops global technology products and platforms that delight our customers and enable our crews to operate our restaurants reliably and effectively. The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing and maintenance of the McDonaldâ€™s restaurant software. Restaurant Technology software includes application user interface, API layer software, data management, and data communication with external systems. The software needs to meet stringent reliability and performance requirements as well as the needs of our customers. The biggest area of increase in our spending has been in technology, which is helping to drive our growth. Weâ€™re looking at how to use technology to improve the customer experience and build new customer experiences. Weâ€™re also exploring technologies that can help us reduce or eliminate repetitive tasks and make employeesâ€™ jobs more exciting and rewarding. With all the new projects and initiatives, it is an exciting time to be on the team that is helping to make a Better McDonald's!Accountabilities & Responsibilities Develop marketing automation workflows focused on marketing communications & experience personalization such as push notifications, emails, and mobile app personalized experiences Conceptualize customer segmentation to support Marketing Automation based on knowledge of pre-existing data structures Translate business requests for marketing capabilities, into clear technical requirements that include data properties needed for implementing marketing automations Technical requirement solicitation and documentation skills to effectively capture and communicate marketing automation solutions/initiatives to key collaborators Ensure that all technical work aligns with the business objectives and marketing strategies Triage issues and defects - capturing, prioritizing and remediating for marketing automations Qualifications Basic Qualifications: Bachelorâ€™s Degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, or similar engineering field or equivalent years of experience. Minimum 1+ years of non-internship professional marketing automation experience with a marketing or advertising automation technology system Experience in implementing marketing automation elements such as segments, audiences, and decision-splits Basic understanding of marketing automation concepts and design principles â€“ proven track record to understand how structured data can be translated into marketing segments and other automations that provide personalized experiences/communications to customers Understanding of core technologies for web content development- HTML, CSS, and JavaScript Extensive experience in working with key data interchange formats including JSON and XML, demonstrating a strong ability to integrate, manipulate, and manage complex data structures across diverse systems and applications Ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams in sophisticated environments Excellent documentation and communication skills to bridge the gap between business strategy and technical teams. Hands on experience with JIRA/Confluence expected Preferred Skills:...

job.job_description: The simple task of buying software, services, or tools at work has become hopelessly complicated at even the most innovative companies in the world. Today, enterprises spend $120T+ per year globally (>30 times larger than annual consumer e-commerce spend) and rely on vendors more than ever before to run their businesses. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, weâ€™re committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. ðŸ“ˆ Start-up equity ðŸ¦· Full health, vision & dental coverage ðŸ½ï¸ Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees ðŸš Commuter benefit ðŸš  Team building events & happy hours ðŸŒ´ Flexible PTO ðŸ’» Apple equipment plus home office budget ðŸ’¸ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We encourage all candidates to apply even if your experience doesn't exactly match up to our job description. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, weâ€™re committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. ðŸ“ˆ Start-up equity ðŸ¦· Full health, vision & dental coverage ðŸ½ï¸ Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees ðŸš Commuter benefit ðŸš  Team building events & happy hours ðŸŒ´ Flexible PTO ðŸ’» Apple equipment plus home office budget ðŸ’¸ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!

One of our core growth strategies is to Double Down on the 3Ds (Delivery, Digital and Drive Thru). The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing and maintenance of the McDonaldâ€™s restaurant software. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. One of our core growth strategies is to Double Down on the 3Ds (Delivery, Digital and Drive Thru). McDonaldâ€™s will accelerate technology innovation so 65M+ customers a day will experience a fast, easy experience, whether at one of our 25,000 and growing Drive thrus, through McDelivery, dine-in or takeaway. The Commercial Product & Platform vision develops global technology products and platforms that delight our customers and enable our crews to operate our restaurants reliably and effectively. The Software Engineer I role works with the Sr Engineering Manager, Chapter Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing and maintenance of the McDonaldâ€™s restaurant software. Our cofounders started Zip in 2020 to address this seemingly intractable problem with a purpose-built procurement platform that provides a simple, consumer-grade user experience. Within the last 4 years, Zip has created a new category and developed the leading solution in this $50B+ TAM space. Today, the worldâ€™s leading companies like OpenAI, Snowflake, Anthropic, Coinbase, and Prudential rely on Zip to manage billions of dollars in spend. We have a world-class team coming from category-defining companies like Airbnb, Meta, Stripe, Salesforce, Apple, and Google. With a $2.2 billion valuation and $370 million in funding from Y Combinator, Tiger Global, BOND, DST Global, and CRV, weâ€™re focused on developing cutting-edge technology, expanding into new global markets, andâ€”above allâ€“driving incredible value for our customers. Join us! Your Role As a Software Engineer you will be responsible for building Zipâ€™s core products and architecture. You will ship features that will be immediately used by our customers, and will work with a tight-knit team that values open communication and cross-functional collaboration. We move quickly to solve a wide range of complex technical and product challenges. While we are an experienced team that can provide constant guidance and mentorship, we value engineers who can scope and solve difficult technical challenges. You Will Design and build highly reliable and resilient products and features Work closely with cross functional product and customer-facing teams to understand requirements and ship thoughtful solutions Write high-quality, extensible, and maintainable code Design and build scalable frontend applications and components Design and build APIs to drive existing and new features for a web-based application Qualifications Pursuing a BS or MS in Computer Science or related technical field involving coding (e.g. physics or math), with a graduation date between December 2025 - June 2026 Experience with web applications and API development. At Zip, our stack includes Python, Javascript/TypeScript, React, and GraphQL Ability and interest to quickly learn new frameworks, architecture patterns, and programming languages as needed Fantastic written and verbal communication skills Prior internships in high-growth startup environment The salary range for this role is $140,000 - $145,000. The salary for this position is determined based on a variety of job-related factors that may include location, relevant experience, education, or particular skills and expertise. Perks & Benefits At Zip, weâ€™re committed to providing our employees with everything they need to do their best work. ðŸ“ˆ Start-up equity ðŸ¦· Full health, vision & dental coverage ðŸ½ï¸ Catered breakfasts, lunches & dinners for SF employees ðŸš Commuter benefit ðŸš  Team building events & happy hours ðŸŒ´ Flexible PTO ðŸ’» Apple equipment plus home office budget ðŸ’¸ 401k plan We're looking to hire Zipsters and that means hiring people who take ownership, communicate openly, have an underdog mindset, and are excited to increase the pace of innovation for every business in the world. We encourage all candidates to apply even if your experience doesn't exactly match up to our job description. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workspace where everyone (regardless of age, religion, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, and more) feels like they belong. We look forward to hearing from you!
